WEBVTT

00:54.793 --> 00:55.528
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

00:55.528 --> 00:56.328
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

00:56.328 --> 00:57.062
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

00:57.062 --> 00:57.796
(for filming child actors and animals.)

01:01.700 --> 01:03.602
I know what you're thinking.

01:03.602 --> 01:05.037
In your imagination,

01:06.071 --> 01:08.207
I've already died at your hands...

01:09.041 --> 01:10.142
countless times.

01:10.609 --> 01:11.443
Imagination?

01:13.312 --> 01:15.748
You dying at my hands is reality.

01:16.081 --> 01:17.116
It's only a matter of time.

01:18.717 --> 01:19.518
Is that so?

01:21.420 --> 01:23.022
You've run away.

01:24.290 --> 01:26.759
Hiding in there like that,
hoping you'll be forgotten...

01:27.459 --> 01:28.561
like an idiot,

01:29.695 --> 01:31.330
living on edge.

01:32.932 --> 01:33.666
Okay.

01:34.700 --> 01:36.669
I guess that's how it might look.

01:39.538 --> 01:41.073
I'm not that smart,

01:41.640 --> 01:43.409
so I hadn't thought that far ahead.

01:44.276 --> 01:45.544
Cut the bullshit.

01:46.579 --> 01:48.814
As long as I'm alive,
that'll never happen.

01:48.814 --> 01:50.115
But here's the thing.

01:51.584 --> 01:52.952
In this world,

01:54.386 --> 01:56.856
nothing is ever as certain
as you make it sound.

01:57.189 --> 01:58.257
Even you...

01:59.024 --> 02:00.226
could change.

02:01.327 --> 02:02.495
So don't be so quick to...

02:06.298 --> 02:08.767
You mean a girl like me
couldn't possibly do anything?

02:09.001 --> 02:11.136
You're just messing around with me...

02:11.136 --> 02:13.506
thinking I'll just ramble on
until I wear myself out and drop.

02:14.673 --> 02:15.574
Right?

02:21.080 --> 02:21.881
Are you insane?

02:23.048 --> 02:24.316
Is it finally sinking in?

02:26.085 --> 02:27.153
Over just this?

02:29.121 --> 02:30.122
I promise you.

02:31.991 --> 02:33.926
You will die at my hands...

02:35.794 --> 02:37.796
no matter what. I swear it.

02:42.368 --> 02:45.571
(Chase)

02:49.575 --> 02:52.578
(CEO Ryu Jun Ho)

03:02.388 --> 03:04.623
Here's the guest list
for next month's groundbreaking ceremony.

03:05.491 --> 03:07.993
We're planning to send invitations
to carefully selected allies.

03:09.094 --> 03:11.096
What should we do about the vice chairman?

03:14.433 --> 03:16.936
He called in the head of legal yesterday
and seems to have given some order.

03:17.503 --> 03:19.638
He keeps digging around into your affairs.

03:20.239 --> 03:22.842
I heard he even ordered
a major expansion of the legal team...

03:22.842 --> 03:24.043
He's a diligent man, that's why.

03:25.878 --> 03:27.847
What should we do about the invitations?

03:29.181 --> 03:30.349
Proceed as planned.

03:30.349 --> 03:32.685
He's still the vice chairman
at headquarters, after all.

03:33.519 --> 03:34.353
Yes, sir.

03:35.287 --> 03:36.121
And...

03:37.056 --> 03:39.391
could you find out
where the vice chairman is right now?

04:15.127 --> 04:17.663
We'll meet when the time comes anyway.

04:18.998 --> 04:20.399
So what kind of rude stunt is this?

04:20.966 --> 04:21.834
My apologies.

04:22.835 --> 04:25.070
As for the person
you were supposed to meet today,

04:25.070 --> 04:27.072
I asked for their understanding.

04:27.072 --> 04:29.742
It seems you and I...

04:30.509 --> 04:32.912
are having a communication problem,
Vice Chairman.

04:34.079 --> 04:34.980
Between me and you,

04:35.648 --> 04:37.750
what communication is needed?

04:38.250 --> 04:40.352
When Mono Architecture was founded,

04:41.587 --> 04:44.657
it was agreed that if the target revenue
was reached within three years,

04:44.657 --> 04:46.158
the shares owned by the company...

04:46.158 --> 04:48.427
would be transferred to Mono Architecture.

04:48.994 --> 04:51.630
And the terms of the transfer
would be decided by mutual agreement.

04:52.064 --> 04:54.433
That's stated quite clearly
in the company's articles of association.

04:56.836 --> 04:57.937
As of last March,

04:58.904 --> 05:01.006
we met the target revenue.

05:01.006 --> 05:03.409
Please honor the agreement.

05:03.409 --> 05:05.611
With the chairman dead,

05:06.946 --> 05:08.180
this is what you bring up?

05:08.414 --> 05:09.215
Vice Chairman.

05:09.215 --> 05:10.950
It may not seem like much to you,

05:12.718 --> 05:14.820
but our company
is in a state of emergency.

05:16.455 --> 05:19.992
The founder was found
reduced to ashes overnight...

05:20.459 --> 05:21.927
burned completely black...

05:22.761 --> 05:25.030
beyond recognition.

05:25.698 --> 05:26.565
And yet,

05:27.867 --> 05:28.801
the police are still...

05:30.236 --> 05:32.738
investigating the cause of his death.

05:34.306 --> 05:35.307
So I have no choice...

05:36.542 --> 05:38.377
but to prepare for the possibility...

05:38.978 --> 05:40.379
that it wasn't a simple accident.

05:41.113 --> 05:42.915
Because we live in a world
where common sense doesn't apply...

05:45.217 --> 05:46.152
like right now.

05:46.452 --> 05:47.319
Vice Chairman.

05:47.319 --> 05:49.722
You don't need
to take my words so personally,

05:50.523 --> 05:52.424
because it's not just me.

05:54.059 --> 05:55.761
It's the company's official position.

05:56.395 --> 05:59.498
I understand you've been poking around...

06:01.867 --> 06:04.603
and looking into my background.

06:05.838 --> 06:07.506
Let's stop wasting...

06:09.041 --> 06:10.009
each other's time.

06:12.378 --> 06:13.746
Are you giving me orders?

06:20.219 --> 06:21.654
You may be...

06:23.389 --> 06:25.157
my senior in this industry, Vice Chairman,

06:27.226 --> 06:29.595
but I'm out of patience now.

06:33.365 --> 06:34.300
From here on out,

06:35.167 --> 06:37.369
even I don't know what I might do.

06:38.037 --> 06:39.171
So you too,

06:39.705 --> 06:40.773
on your own,

06:41.373 --> 06:43.142
should think before you act.

06:43.576 --> 06:44.443
You little punk!

06:48.047 --> 06:49.014
Well then,

06:49.014 --> 06:51.750
I'll consider this
a productive conversation,

06:52.518 --> 06:53.786
and take my leave.

07:40.466 --> 07:42.334
Have you ever really felt anxious?

07:52.878 --> 07:55.447
The kind where everything collapses
in an instant,

07:58.617 --> 08:00.119
and you're terrified...

08:00.119 --> 08:02.254
someone might do that to your life.

08:07.526 --> 08:08.561
Sometimes,

08:10.262 --> 08:12.631
I want to let go of everything.

08:16.435 --> 08:17.937
I'm just too exhausted.

08:22.875 --> 08:24.109
It's too hard.

08:31.817 --> 08:33.486
I shouldn't have gone.

08:35.454 --> 08:36.322
That day,

08:40.392 --> 08:42.461
I went somewhere I never should have.

08:43.395 --> 08:44.196
Do you see that?

08:45.331 --> 08:46.198
Yeah.

08:46.198 --> 08:47.466
That's where we went.

08:48.033 --> 08:48.901
I see.

08:54.974 --> 08:55.875
He's here.

08:56.675 --> 08:57.877
Myo Jin, let's go.

09:03.182 --> 09:05.384
Ryu Jun Ho.

09:09.788 --> 09:12.124
I missed you.

09:24.703 --> 09:25.838
What do you think?

09:28.374 --> 09:29.208
Tell me.

09:34.513 --> 09:35.781
What's with these furnitures?

09:37.216 --> 09:40.653
They're not what I asked you to order.

09:40.653 --> 09:41.654
Why?

09:41.854 --> 09:43.422
They're almost exactly what you described,

09:44.123 --> 09:45.191
just more expensive.

09:46.625 --> 09:47.693
What happened...

09:49.962 --> 09:52.498
to everything I said?

09:52.832 --> 09:55.100
I told you, I picked better pieces.

09:55.701 --> 09:56.468
You don't like it?

09:56.468 --> 09:58.404
It's not that I don't like it. It's wrong.

10:00.239 --> 10:02.541
I told the contractor
every detail myself...

10:02.541 --> 10:03.876
and even wrote it all down,

10:03.876 --> 10:05.444
and you overturned every bit of it.

10:05.444 --> 10:07.046
Are you getting mad at me right now?

10:11.851 --> 10:13.219
If you hate it that much,

10:18.123 --> 10:19.191
throw them all out.

10:21.660 --> 10:23.963
Tear it all apart
and fill it with what you want.

10:25.297 --> 10:26.198
Problem solved.

10:26.632 --> 10:28.801
Architecture isn't just the exterior.

10:28.801 --> 10:30.536
The interior is part
of the architecture too.

10:30.936 --> 10:32.738
This may be a vacation house
for you and me,

10:32.738 --> 10:33.739
but...

10:33.739 --> 10:35.908
it's still one of my works in Korea.

10:36.308 --> 10:37.343
That's right.

10:37.810 --> 10:40.446
This is a space just for the two of us.

10:41.881 --> 10:43.582
I love it just the way it is.

10:44.150 --> 10:47.086
If I'm happy with it,
shouldn't you be too?

10:54.360 --> 10:56.662
Please, can you stop
playing the perfectionist...

10:57.863 --> 10:59.365
for once?

11:00.399 --> 11:01.233
Please.

11:03.903 --> 11:05.104
You greedy young man.

11:10.943 --> 11:11.811
Say hi.

11:12.144 --> 11:13.412
That's my friend, Myo Jin.

11:25.591 --> 11:26.692
You know who he is, right?

11:35.167 --> 11:37.403
You have a house like this
in every country?

11:37.770 --> 11:39.572
The others were all built to be sold,

11:40.673 --> 11:41.941
but not this one.

11:45.711 --> 11:48.781
I heard who designed this place,
so I said I wanted it.

11:49.215 --> 11:50.049
The design?

11:52.017 --> 11:53.352
Half of it was done by someone else.

11:54.587 --> 11:55.588
Are we really doing this again?

11:57.022 --> 11:57.823
Cheers.

12:03.429 --> 12:06.499
But your father is really impressive.

12:07.066 --> 12:09.235
I can't even imagine...

12:09.235 --> 12:10.369
how huge his business must be.

12:12.071 --> 12:14.740
Myo Jin is so curious about my dad.

12:15.674 --> 12:17.376
She talks about him to me all the time.

12:21.847 --> 12:22.815
But...

12:23.282 --> 12:24.216
the two of you...

12:26.385 --> 12:27.586
are so alike.

12:28.554 --> 12:29.488
In what way?

12:29.488 --> 12:30.789
The way you two admire my dad.

12:31.857 --> 12:33.459
You say it all the time too,

12:33.459 --> 12:35.094
that you want to be
as successful as my dad.

12:37.429 --> 12:39.365
Myo Jin says it every chance she gets too,

12:39.365 --> 12:40.900
that she wants to meet my dad.

12:43.269 --> 12:44.103
Really?

12:44.436 --> 12:46.205
Was I like that?

12:46.205 --> 12:47.072
Yeah.

12:47.072 --> 12:49.742
He said he'd be coming
to Korea before long anyway,

12:50.242 --> 12:51.410
so I guess you'll get your chance then.

12:51.911 --> 12:53.112
The three of us should meet him together.

12:53.879 --> 12:55.381
Is he planning to come?

12:55.948 --> 12:58.551
I don't know. Maybe he just says that.

13:00.719 --> 13:01.587
Cheers.

13:27.313 --> 13:28.814
I'm just going to run to the bath...

13:50.169 --> 13:51.103
Ms. Ham.

13:52.171 --> 13:53.339
I'm sorry.

13:53.339 --> 13:55.608
I thought you were Hee Su.

13:56.075 --> 13:57.543
It's okay.

13:57.543 --> 13:58.711
It was my fault.

13:59.044 --> 14:00.646
I shouldn't have borrowed
Hee Su's clothes.

14:01.814 --> 14:03.516
I didn't know I'd be staying until today.

14:04.517 --> 14:05.518
I'm sorry.

14:06.752 --> 14:07.920
I'm not even drunk,

14:08.521 --> 14:10.156
and I still made that mistake.

14:10.856 --> 14:11.857
I'm sorry.

14:14.827 --> 14:16.195
Jun Ho.

14:17.329 --> 14:19.565
Did we finish all the champagne?

14:20.699 --> 14:21.867
There's none left?

14:28.474 --> 14:31.977
That looks great on you.

14:32.711 --> 14:34.346
You should've changed sooner.

14:35.080 --> 14:35.981
Right.

14:36.282 --> 14:38.017
Why are you all by yourself?
Isn't that boring?

14:38.517 --> 14:39.418
Let's drink more.

14:40.419 --> 14:41.520
I'm done.

14:41.987 --> 14:43.255
I'm going to get some air.

14:43.255 --> 14:44.123
Why?

14:44.557 --> 14:45.524
Are you feeling stuffy?

14:46.392 --> 14:48.427
Should we take the yacht out to sea then?

14:48.627 --> 14:50.930
No. You two spend some time together.

15:13.752 --> 15:14.553
Stop.

15:14.820 --> 15:15.688
Stop.

15:17.490 --> 15:18.390
Why?

15:19.592 --> 15:20.626
I said stop.

15:23.429 --> 15:24.396
Why, all of a sudden?

15:28.634 --> 15:29.869
The air is off.

15:32.238 --> 15:33.339
Everything feels different.

15:50.523 --> 15:51.724
Are you still taking the pills?

15:53.259 --> 15:54.160
Why?

15:54.860 --> 15:55.861
Are you worried?

15:58.831 --> 16:00.733
What are you doing? Give me that.

16:00.733 --> 16:02.001
Let go of this. Are you crazy?

16:02.001 --> 16:04.336
I told you not to keep
increasing the dose on your own.

16:12.044 --> 16:12.878
You...

16:14.613 --> 16:16.148
really are crazy.

16:18.851 --> 16:20.319
You haven't forgotten...

16:21.821 --> 16:23.155
what Dad told you, have you?

16:24.190 --> 16:25.791
He's not giving you the gifts...

16:27.693 --> 16:29.461
for nothing.

16:31.931 --> 16:32.832
You know that, right?

17:17.910 --> 17:18.744
Get in.

17:19.178 --> 17:20.012
Excuse me?

17:20.546 --> 17:21.514
I said get in.

17:59.118 --> 18:00.986
Is something going on
between you and Hee Su?

18:02.154 --> 18:04.924
Since when have you been
so close with Hee Su?

18:08.360 --> 18:09.428
You probably know...

18:10.930 --> 18:13.065
that she's not easy to get close to.

18:19.839 --> 18:20.773
She's...

18:21.941 --> 18:22.975
my friend.

18:23.776 --> 18:24.643
Hee Su...

18:25.544 --> 18:28.214
seems to really care about you, Ms. Ham.

18:29.048 --> 18:29.982
What is it...

18:31.650 --> 18:33.052
that you like about Hee Su?

18:35.821 --> 18:37.456
Please be understanding, Mr. Ryu.

18:39.024 --> 18:42.061
When women haven't seen their lover
in a while, they fuss a little.

18:43.562 --> 18:45.130
Hee Su is just...

18:46.265 --> 18:47.833
more soft-hearted than other women.

18:58.744 --> 18:59.745
You seem to know...

19:00.713 --> 19:01.847
quite a lot about Hee Su.

19:03.782 --> 19:05.184
You should go back now.

19:06.986 --> 19:09.188
I'll stay out a little longer.

19:09.588 --> 19:10.856
Aren't you curious?

19:13.425 --> 19:14.260
About what?

19:14.693 --> 19:16.662
Whether what happened earlier
was really an accident.

19:19.498 --> 19:21.100
I know you know...

19:23.802 --> 19:25.204
it wasn't, Ms. Ham.

19:26.839 --> 19:28.107
Go back.

19:29.141 --> 19:30.910
I don't want to cause
pointless misunderstandings.

19:31.310 --> 19:33.245
What misunderstanding?

20:28.534 --> 20:31.437
I stole Jun Ho away from Hee Su.

20:33.105 --> 20:34.573
I was out of my mind.

20:35.808 --> 20:38.043
I betrayed my friendship with Hee Su,

20:38.777 --> 20:40.646
hid it as if nothing had happened,

20:40.646 --> 20:42.314
and pretended not to know anything.

20:49.955 --> 20:50.990
Did Hee Su...

20:51.957 --> 20:52.825
really...

20:56.028 --> 20:57.630
know nothing?

21:28.794 --> 21:30.329
Were you at the beach?

21:38.337 --> 21:39.305
Yeah.

21:50.649 --> 21:52.017
What took you so long?

21:54.286 --> 21:55.254
Well,

21:55.855 --> 21:58.190
I stayed out a bit longer than I meant to.

21:59.325 --> 22:00.526
It looks like you had fun.

22:06.532 --> 22:07.466
What about Jun Ho?

22:07.733 --> 22:08.601
What?

22:08.834 --> 22:11.136
Did you see Jun Ho?

22:12.404 --> 22:14.406
I thought he was heading
toward the beach, too.

22:16.242 --> 22:18.043
I wouldn't know.

22:24.683 --> 22:25.718
Isn't it funny?

22:27.987 --> 22:30.156
What is?

22:30.789 --> 22:32.458
Everyone thinks...

22:35.027 --> 22:37.129
they're faster than the tide.

22:38.831 --> 22:39.932
But seawater...

22:41.867 --> 22:43.435
rushes in faster than you'd think.

22:45.271 --> 22:47.239
By the time you realize it,
it'll already be too late.

22:48.707 --> 22:49.775
Before you know it,

22:51.043 --> 22:52.845
you're already in over your head.

23:00.286 --> 23:01.420
So...

23:01.787 --> 23:02.855
be careful.

23:13.432 --> 23:14.567
You must be tired too.

23:37.756 --> 23:39.058
This is yours, right, Ms. Ham?

23:43.162 --> 23:44.029
Give it to me.

23:44.563 --> 23:45.698
Hee Su was right.

23:47.032 --> 23:47.833
About what?

23:48.267 --> 23:50.069
She said you're a very good painter,

23:50.669 --> 23:52.071
and that I should buy
your work in advance.

23:53.339 --> 23:54.573
Hee Su was joking.

23:56.909 --> 23:58.811
Don't you know
Hee Su never jokes like that?

24:01.647 --> 24:04.216
Ms. Ham, do you paint people too?

24:04.817 --> 24:07.186
If you need a portrait,
please ask Hee Su.

24:09.321 --> 24:10.723
She's much better at it than I am.

24:11.924 --> 24:13.492
Of course Hee Su is good too,

24:14.493 --> 24:15.327
but...

24:16.929 --> 24:18.497
I'm curious about your work.

24:23.836 --> 24:24.803
One mistake...

24:25.437 --> 24:26.672
was enough.

24:27.239 --> 24:30.176
I'm in so much pain I want to die,
so stop playing these games.

24:32.077 --> 24:34.580
- Ms. Ham.
- Even this talk makes me uncomfortable.

24:35.548 --> 24:37.216
You said you're going to Seoul
tomorrow morning, right?

24:39.084 --> 24:40.352
I'm going tomorrow too.

24:41.253 --> 24:42.421
My office...

24:43.455 --> 24:45.124
isn't far from Hee Su's house.

24:45.124 --> 24:47.126
- Please, stop...
- Mono Architecture.

24:48.194 --> 24:49.962
It'll come up in your GPS,
so come by anytime.

25:02.942 --> 25:04.043
Trash.

25:06.745 --> 25:09.682
I was trash and a devil to Hee Su.

25:12.751 --> 25:13.986
I ruined everything,

25:13.986 --> 25:15.788
and I stabbed Hee Su in the back.

25:23.629 --> 25:26.499
Do you know what it's like
to be born into a pit...

25:28.534 --> 25:29.435
of desert sand?

25:31.203 --> 25:32.738
You wash your body with sand,

25:34.940 --> 25:37.309
eat sand like it's food,

25:40.146 --> 25:42.581
and die with that grit
grinding through you.

25:46.152 --> 25:48.154
That's me now.

25:54.693 --> 25:56.695
Jun Ho betrayed Hee Su too.

25:58.697 --> 26:01.367
He deceived her and broke her,
just like I did.

26:04.069 --> 26:06.438
We made a choice we can never take back,

26:08.307 --> 26:10.576
and Hee Su suffered to death all alone.

26:14.446 --> 26:17.349
Ugly beasts named
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho...

26:18.217 --> 26:19.652
killed Hee Su.

26:24.390 --> 26:26.692
She must have been so lonely
and in so much pain.

26:36.135 --> 26:37.136
Even now,

26:39.839 --> 26:41.607
I want to pay the price.

27:39.598 --> 27:40.733
Why did you do this?

27:45.638 --> 27:47.873
Setting aside whether it's good or bad,

27:47.873 --> 27:51.177
this is nothing more than
a piece made for personal gratification.

27:52.578 --> 27:54.313
There isn't a single element...

27:54.313 --> 27:56.148
that fits the traditional
object-based style.

28:01.187 --> 28:02.054
Thank you.

28:03.722 --> 28:07.760
You've understood my intent exactly, sir.

28:08.060 --> 28:11.030
This project is about building
the largest museum in Asia...

28:11.030 --> 28:12.898
here in Korea.

28:13.499 --> 28:16.936
Not only in scale, but in artistry,
technical skill, and creativity,

28:16.936 --> 28:17.903
in every way,

28:18.404 --> 28:21.173
it will become a benchmark
for Korean architecture.

28:21.173 --> 28:22.374
With a design like this,

28:23.909 --> 28:26.712
what exactly can you claim
as your strength, Mr. Ryu?

28:27.346 --> 28:28.180
Sir,

28:29.315 --> 28:32.918
when most architects begin a new project,

28:33.886 --> 28:36.789
they start by referencing past typologies.

28:37.423 --> 28:40.092
But as an architect,

28:41.360 --> 28:42.495
I reject that approach.

28:42.495 --> 28:45.431
Too much confidence
can come off as arrogance.

28:45.431 --> 28:47.800
Repeated reference to past cases...

28:49.401 --> 28:51.871
only leads to
the accumulation of imitation.

28:52.938 --> 28:55.207
If we cannot break free from that frame,

28:55.207 --> 28:57.042
Korean architecture will eventually...

28:57.042 --> 28:59.245
harden into a series of similar forms.

29:00.813 --> 29:03.382
You may criticize my work,

29:05.184 --> 29:07.720
but the more efforts and attempts
like mine accumulate,

29:07.720 --> 29:08.754
the more Korean architecture...

29:10.789 --> 29:12.925
will break free from self-replication.

29:14.960 --> 29:17.363
That's why for this museum,

29:17.363 --> 29:19.698
I chose "Silence for Essence"
as the concept.

29:21.634 --> 29:24.103
By thoroughly eliminating
the interference...

29:24.103 --> 29:26.472
and imposed functions
of conventional buildings,

29:26.472 --> 29:29.375
I want to focus...

29:30.075 --> 29:31.844
on faithfully holding the people, music,

29:31.844 --> 29:34.780
and essence of life within it.

29:46.725 --> 29:49.094
(Made in China,
HGA Distribution Co., Ltd.)

29:51.063 --> 29:52.898
Speak clearly, you bastard.

29:53.933 --> 29:55.734
What did I do so wrong?

29:56.001 --> 29:57.436
All I did was...

29:57.870 --> 29:59.605
take a little nap after lunch.
Is that such a crime?

29:59.872 --> 30:03.209
I gave my work to other guys instead.

30:03.843 --> 30:07.513
So in the end, I didn't cause any loss.

30:07.513 --> 30:08.380
That's what I'm saying.

30:09.248 --> 30:12.384
That bastard sure talks a lot.

30:13.686 --> 30:15.855
If beating up
a perfectly fine site manager...

30:16.388 --> 30:18.557
isn't wrong, then what is?

30:19.859 --> 30:23.629
That site manager had it in for me.

30:23.929 --> 30:26.532
He's always trailing behind me...

30:27.032 --> 30:28.701
and picking fights
whenever he gets a chance.

30:29.502 --> 30:30.769
What was I supposed to do?

30:31.370 --> 30:33.038
There's a limit...

30:34.807 --> 30:36.108
to how much a person can take.

30:36.108 --> 30:37.576
Hey.

30:37.810 --> 30:38.711
Are you a credit card...

30:39.278 --> 30:40.112
to have a limit?

30:41.046 --> 30:43.082
It's nice to meet a bastard
even dumber than me.

30:43.415 --> 30:45.151
Listen to him ramble
like he's something special.

30:45.417 --> 30:47.920
Hey, if you're getting paid,
just do the work you're told.

30:48.320 --> 30:49.155
While everyone else was working,

30:49.155 --> 30:51.123
what was so great about you
lying there asleep by yourself...

30:51.123 --> 30:52.992
to beat a man up over that, you bastard?

30:53.726 --> 30:54.760
Do you want me to show you how it's done?

30:55.394 --> 30:56.328
Do you?

30:56.529 --> 30:57.730
I'll split your whole unit.

31:00.466 --> 31:02.468
Did everything I told you
already vanish from that thick skull?

31:03.903 --> 31:05.304
What was it you told me?

31:05.604 --> 31:07.840
That ignorant bastard is stupid too.

31:07.840 --> 31:09.341
That's exactly why
he keeps causing trouble.

31:10.876 --> 31:13.913
If you go around acting like a thug
in someone else's country,

31:14.280 --> 31:16.515
all our people get cursed for it.

31:16.515 --> 31:18.117
Didn't I say that?

31:22.021 --> 31:25.090
The reason Korean Chinese folks like us
don't get treated right...

31:25.090 --> 31:26.592
is because idiots like him...

31:26.592 --> 31:29.128
keep causing trouble for other people.

31:29.728 --> 31:30.896
Didn't I say that?

31:30.896 --> 31:32.198
You don't remember a thing?

31:32.565 --> 31:33.866
I remember.

31:35.935 --> 31:36.969
I remember.

31:36.969 --> 31:37.837
What?

31:39.538 --> 31:41.040
So you remembered and still did it?

31:45.044 --> 31:46.011
Then,

31:46.645 --> 31:47.680
because of you,

31:49.281 --> 31:51.851
our fellow Korean Chinese
are going to get cursed again.

31:53.886 --> 31:54.987
How are you going
to take responsibility for that?

31:55.254 --> 31:56.956
Boss, I'm sorry.

31:57.857 --> 32:00.759
From now on, I won't even eat or work out.

32:00.759 --> 32:01.961
I'll only work.

32:05.498 --> 32:06.932
That blockheaded bastard.

32:07.299 --> 32:09.802
Keep him reflecting on what he did
until I say otherwise.

32:09.802 --> 32:11.770
Boss, please spare me.

32:12.037 --> 32:13.239
I'm sorry.

32:13.239 --> 32:14.840
Please, just spare me this once.

32:14.840 --> 32:15.741
Boss.

32:15.975 --> 32:16.842
Boss!

32:17.543 --> 32:19.278
- Please spare me.
- Shut your mouth.

32:19.545 --> 32:21.313
People will think
you're being dragged off to die.

32:22.148 --> 32:24.250
Boss.

32:25.317 --> 32:26.252
Boss.

32:27.052 --> 32:28.387
We've got a problem.

32:28.387 --> 32:29.388
Hae Sik...

32:30.122 --> 32:32.558
got beaten by some gangsters
and hauled off to the hospital.

32:32.558 --> 32:34.360
Who this time?

32:34.827 --> 32:36.662
Your younger brother, Hae Sik.

32:44.837 --> 32:45.938
This isn't fair.

32:47.339 --> 32:49.308
I even got disciplined at work today,

32:50.342 --> 32:52.711
and now look at the state I'm in.

32:53.312 --> 32:55.247
Is what you told me all there is to say?

32:55.781 --> 32:57.449
So you did absolutely nothing wrong?

32:57.449 --> 32:58.617
Don't you know me, Hae Kwang?

32:59.819 --> 33:02.955
Have you ever seen me
go around making trouble?

33:03.389 --> 33:04.256
Because of me,

33:05.257 --> 33:07.326
has our people ever lost face,

33:07.326 --> 33:08.294
even once?

33:08.828 --> 33:10.196
Have I ever, even once...

33:12.865 --> 33:14.466
Even seeing me like this,

33:15.267 --> 33:17.536
you're saying
you still can't trust your brother?

33:20.539 --> 33:22.141
Do you remember where it was?

33:22.141 --> 33:24.143
I don't know where the ones
who did this to me are,

33:24.710 --> 33:26.846
but I do know
where the guy who drugged our drinks is.

33:27.980 --> 33:29.648
My friend gets discharged tomorrow,

33:30.583 --> 33:32.151
so you can ask him.

33:33.018 --> 33:34.720
Why didn't you say anything until now?

33:35.087 --> 33:37.456
You obviously just got back from home
after a long time.

33:37.890 --> 33:39.792
This is nothing to be proud of.

33:42.027 --> 33:45.231
It's humiliating enough
getting beaten up in a foreign country.

33:46.365 --> 33:47.399
If people start saying...

33:47.933 --> 33:49.635
I'm an idiot,

33:50.269 --> 33:52.204
what happens to my pride?

33:52.204 --> 33:53.138
Your pride?

33:53.539 --> 33:56.475
Then out of all those guys,
why did you get beaten the worst?

33:58.077 --> 34:00.146
If I don't look out
for my own people, who will?

34:00.746 --> 34:01.647
Do you think...

34:01.647 --> 34:04.350
I wanted to get beaten like this?

34:08.120 --> 34:09.054
It hurts.

34:10.156 --> 34:11.190
Fine.

34:14.693 --> 34:16.228
Look at the mess you're in.

34:20.833 --> 34:21.767
Hey.

34:21.767 --> 34:24.737
Who's that bitch hanging around with now?

34:24.737 --> 34:27.006
She'll be contacting you again
before long, won't she?

34:28.040 --> 34:30.209
Just give me the signal when she does,

34:30.209 --> 34:31.710
and I'll take care
of everything after that.

34:34.513 --> 34:36.715
How many times
do I have to say this to you?

34:36.715 --> 34:38.551
I'm repeating the same thing
like a parrot.

34:39.418 --> 34:40.319
If...

34:40.719 --> 34:42.521
that woman comes here,

34:43.022 --> 34:44.623
and I tell you about it,

34:46.525 --> 34:48.527
you'll handle it yourself, is that it?

34:48.527 --> 34:49.829
And you'll just...

34:50.362 --> 34:52.331
sit back and enjoy the show.

34:52.898 --> 34:53.933
Why?

34:54.500 --> 34:55.334
What?

34:55.668 --> 34:57.770
Why drag me into something...

34:58.137 --> 34:59.538
you can do by yourself?

35:00.339 --> 35:01.674
What are you saying?

35:02.041 --> 35:03.175
Do you want me to spell it out?

35:13.919 --> 35:15.387
If that woman dies,

35:17.590 --> 35:20.059
you'll be the one who did it,

35:20.426 --> 35:22.628
but the blood will end up on my hands.

35:22.895 --> 35:24.864
If you act alone,

35:25.264 --> 35:26.098
since...

35:26.966 --> 35:29.268
I would know it was your doing,

35:31.637 --> 35:33.339
you'd be afraid of what comes after.

35:33.639 --> 35:37.143
And after getting rid of her,
you'd have to get rid of me too.

35:38.377 --> 35:40.012
So...

35:41.180 --> 35:42.515
you've been thinking it over.

35:44.083 --> 35:45.784
That's why, from the start,

35:47.920 --> 35:50.055
you want to pull me in.

35:52.091 --> 35:54.293
No, I think you've got the wrong idea.

35:54.293 --> 35:56.495
You think you can play
a shallow game like that?

35:58.030 --> 36:00.065
Someone like you who became
the driver for a wealthy family...

36:01.400 --> 36:04.003
from a day laborer on construction sites?

36:09.742 --> 36:11.177
Bring money!

36:12.444 --> 36:14.180
Whatever your angle is,

36:14.180 --> 36:16.148
I'll do exactly what you want.

36:18.784 --> 36:19.985
Did you already forget...

36:20.619 --> 36:22.488
what it takes to get me moving?

36:30.462 --> 36:33.866
If you come empty-handed one more time
and try that slick shit with me,

36:34.934 --> 36:36.268
not that woman,

36:37.269 --> 36:39.338
but you will die at my hands first.

36:42.641 --> 36:44.477
If you understand, then get out.

36:47.179 --> 36:48.280
I'm tired.

37:07.266 --> 37:08.200
You're still awake?

37:15.174 --> 37:16.108
Are you okay?

37:17.042 --> 37:18.410
There's something I want to ask.

37:19.745 --> 37:21.247
Will you answer me honestly?

37:24.216 --> 37:25.050
Yeah.

37:26.018 --> 37:26.886
What is it?

37:34.593 --> 37:36.061
It's about Choi Hee Su.

37:37.530 --> 37:40.833
Why haven't you told me until now
about the relationship between you two?

37:44.036 --> 37:46.305
- Myo Jin.
- "Just someone you barely know?"

37:47.806 --> 37:48.707
How...

37:49.642 --> 37:51.610
How could you lie like that?

37:54.914 --> 37:57.750
It was too hard for you to take
because you were in treatment, Myo Jin.

38:00.986 --> 38:03.489
You abandoned Hee Su,
who was your girlfriend,

38:04.256 --> 38:05.958
and I betrayed Hee Su, who was my friend.

38:05.958 --> 38:07.259
Is that what you call "too hard?"

38:08.694 --> 38:09.528
No.

38:10.696 --> 38:12.932
That's something I need to know.

38:15.234 --> 38:16.001
Myo Jin.

38:16.001 --> 38:17.803
You said you couldn't tell me
because you were afraid it would shock me,

38:18.437 --> 38:20.773
and that you'd tell me everything
once I got better.

38:21.907 --> 38:24.677
Was that all about Hee Su,
who was abandoned by trash like us,

38:25.678 --> 38:28.247
and then died in an accident?

38:43.195 --> 38:44.029
I'm sorry.

38:46.932 --> 38:48.167
I was selfish.

38:55.875 --> 38:58.010
But I wasn't trying to hide it on purpose.

38:58.944 --> 39:00.646
How could I?

39:03.516 --> 39:06.652
Those are memories
that would've come back eventually.

39:07.653 --> 39:09.889
It was hard for me to say,

39:11.190 --> 39:12.158
and for you, Myo Jin,

39:13.025 --> 39:14.426
it would be hard to hear.

39:16.162 --> 39:17.096
I think...

39:18.264 --> 39:19.632
I just wanted to put it off
a little longer.

39:21.133 --> 39:22.401
This is all my fault.

39:24.703 --> 39:26.572
Hee Su was struggling.

39:28.874 --> 39:31.977
She said everyone around her
only wanted to use her,

39:31.977 --> 39:33.212
and that she was all alone.

39:34.547 --> 39:35.581
The only people...

39:36.448 --> 39:38.617
she thought she could trust
were you and me.

39:39.685 --> 39:41.954
Hee Su was already wavering.

39:48.894 --> 39:50.563
Every time I try to do anything,

39:50.563 --> 39:52.498
things keep going wrong.

40:05.211 --> 40:06.712
What happened to Hee Su?

40:08.214 --> 40:10.883
The investigation is still underway,
so we'll learn in time.

40:11.450 --> 40:14.687
What was I doing there that day?

40:16.489 --> 40:17.756
Like the detective said,

40:18.390 --> 40:20.759
no matter how hard I think about
why my accident happened near the villa,

40:21.961 --> 40:23.963
I just can't remember.

40:34.640 --> 40:35.541
What?

40:35.774 --> 40:37.910
Choi Hee Su's account was deleted.

40:38.244 --> 40:40.379
Forensics had a rough time finding this.

40:40.813 --> 40:43.682
Come on, she's a young woman
with U.S. citizenship.

40:43.682 --> 40:45.618
How could she have no social media?

40:46.185 --> 40:47.520
Someone must've wiped it.

40:48.154 --> 40:49.989
She could've deleted it herself.

40:50.923 --> 40:52.158
It was after the incident.

40:52.791 --> 40:53.859
That's when it was deleted.

40:54.293 --> 40:55.127
No way.

41:00.966 --> 41:02.835
Choi Hee Su and Ham Myo Jin
knew each other?

41:03.435 --> 41:04.303
Friends?

41:05.237 --> 41:07.339
Hey, what does this look like to you?

41:08.174 --> 41:10.075
This was taken to celebrate an engagement.

41:11.177 --> 41:12.178
Choi Hee Su...

41:13.045 --> 41:13.979
and Ryu Jun Ho?

41:15.548 --> 41:17.149
That Ham Myo Jin...

41:17.783 --> 41:18.918
is seriously creepy.

41:19.451 --> 41:22.221
She kept insisting
she didn't know anything,

41:22.221 --> 41:23.722
and here's the reason.

41:25.357 --> 41:27.626
After Choi Hee Su died in an accident,

41:27.626 --> 41:29.762
her friend Ham Myo Jin
stepped right into her place?

41:32.264 --> 41:34.466
But she keeps denying it
with that same old routine.

41:35.801 --> 41:37.770
Maybe there's really
something wrong with her head.

41:41.674 --> 41:43.843
You took time out
of your busy schedule for me,

41:44.210 --> 41:45.845
so I hope you like it.

41:46.445 --> 41:49.215
I've booked dinner
at a very special place.

41:51.217 --> 41:52.251
When have you ever...

41:52.885 --> 41:54.520
done anything that wasn't special?

42:02.228 --> 42:03.696
The way things are looking,

42:03.696 --> 42:07.733
Oh Sang Il will likely become
head of the judging panel.

42:09.001 --> 42:12.505
The other judges are unanimously
recommending him too.

42:13.005 --> 42:14.206
Not just me,

42:14.206 --> 42:17.009
but everyone in the industry is on edge.

42:17.009 --> 42:18.277
On edge? Please.

42:19.178 --> 42:20.613
There are only a few firms...

42:20.946 --> 42:23.482
that can handle
a project like this anyway.

42:25.518 --> 42:27.052
I will make sure this goes successful.

42:27.319 --> 42:30.689
I know your abilities well, Mr. Cho.

42:32.558 --> 42:33.492
But tell me,

42:34.760 --> 42:37.229
do you happen to know Ryu Jun Ho?

42:37.897 --> 42:39.398
He's still young,

42:39.398 --> 42:40.799
but he has the fundamentals.

42:41.400 --> 42:43.202
He hasn't been back in Korea long,

42:43.569 --> 42:45.604
but the projects he's done
aren't bad either.

42:46.972 --> 42:48.207
But why do you ask?

42:48.474 --> 42:50.643
I heard that young man...

42:50.643 --> 42:52.878
secretly met with CEO Oh Sang Il.

42:54.180 --> 42:55.714
The timing is rather sensitive, isn't it?

42:56.882 --> 42:58.751
He doesn't have
enough domestic work history,

42:58.751 --> 43:00.352
so he shouldn't even qualify to apply.

43:00.352 --> 43:01.921
The qualifications were already announced.

43:02.888 --> 43:03.956
You know that next week,

43:03.956 --> 43:06.992
the judging panel
is being announced, right?

43:07.226 --> 43:08.093
Yes, Assemblyman.

43:08.928 --> 43:09.795
At that time,

43:11.664 --> 43:15.134
I think the revised clause
will be announced as well.

43:15.601 --> 43:18.938
Oh Sang Il personally requested it
from the other judges.

43:19.672 --> 43:21.740
He said there should be
merit-based judging...

43:21.740 --> 43:23.943
without sacred cows or discrimination.

43:24.577 --> 43:25.444
That does sound...

43:26.078 --> 43:28.314
exactly like CEO Oh.

43:29.815 --> 43:31.116
Even if it's you,

43:31.817 --> 43:33.586
don't get too complacent.

43:34.620 --> 43:36.989
There's always a back door somewhere.

43:47.032 --> 43:48.067
I'm sorry...

43:49.635 --> 43:52.037
for barging in
during your break like this.

43:52.037 --> 43:53.672
Like your memories, Ms. Ham?

43:58.844 --> 44:01.113
Before Jun Ho met me,

44:01.113 --> 44:03.182
he was already engaged to someone.

44:05.017 --> 44:06.886
I was friends with her.

44:07.520 --> 44:08.921
I don't know why I did it,

44:10.823 --> 44:13.626
but I ended up realizing
that I stole her fiancé.

44:18.864 --> 44:20.633
I wandered around...

44:20.633 --> 44:22.701
as if I'd find something profound,

44:25.137 --> 44:26.639
and the memory I found...

44:29.275 --> 44:30.376
was that I was trash.

44:34.513 --> 44:35.314
Doctor,

44:36.715 --> 44:39.218
is there any point
in continuing my treatment?

44:41.587 --> 44:42.555
Tell me...

44:43.055 --> 44:45.758
the honest thought
inside your heart, Ms. Ham.

44:47.593 --> 44:48.661
I'm afraid.

44:50.763 --> 44:52.965
I'm already in so much pain I want to die,

44:55.034 --> 44:56.769
and if there's still
something worse waiting,

44:57.703 --> 44:58.804
if that's really true...

44:58.804 --> 45:01.440
All of this is for you to decide, Ms. Ham.

45:02.107 --> 45:03.876
It always has been.

45:04.910 --> 45:06.412
I've only helped from the side...

45:06.412 --> 45:07.546
in a very limited way.

45:09.782 --> 45:12.117
Human memory becomes distorted.

45:12.751 --> 45:14.753
Initial memories...

45:14.753 --> 45:16.489
are almost never preserved intact...

45:16.489 --> 45:17.690
for anyone.

45:18.357 --> 45:19.558
Distortion?

45:20.593 --> 45:23.062
Time changes everything.

45:23.662 --> 45:25.231
Memory is no different.

45:26.966 --> 45:30.102
In a case like yours,
after such a major accident,

45:30.736 --> 45:33.672
we need to judge
the situation more carefully.

45:35.241 --> 45:37.243
Stealing your friend's lover,

45:37.243 --> 45:39.311
and then saying
you don't know why you did it...

45:39.945 --> 45:41.780
is avoidance or an excuse.

45:42.882 --> 45:44.283
Doctor, that really isn't...

45:44.283 --> 45:45.951
I know. It's neither.

45:46.252 --> 45:48.354
As a doctor, the Myo Jin I know...

45:50.990 --> 45:52.324
truly doesn't know...

45:52.324 --> 45:54.293
why she acted that way.

45:54.960 --> 45:55.961
Then...

45:55.961 --> 45:57.129
It will be hard,

45:57.129 --> 45:59.298
but try to be patient a little longer.

46:00.132 --> 46:01.867
The truth may be...

46:02.401 --> 46:05.070
different from what you think, Ms. Ham.

46:06.238 --> 46:09.175
Could that really be true?

46:10.709 --> 46:11.811
Let's wait and see.

46:13.579 --> 46:14.914
You're already moving...

46:14.914 --> 46:17.783
in a much better direction now.

46:23.756 --> 46:26.225
(Jigu Electronics)

46:28.928 --> 46:30.629
No, that's a lie.

46:31.230 --> 46:33.199
That day, that bastard brought...

46:33.199 --> 46:35.968
everything to our table himself
including the drinks and the food.

46:41.907 --> 46:44.877
What's that idiot babbling about?

46:44.877 --> 46:45.945
To leave no evidence,

46:45.945 --> 46:48.314
he left the card payments alone
and only took cash.

46:49.014 --> 46:51.584
And when he handed us over to that thug,
he probably got paid again.

46:51.584 --> 46:52.885
Double-dipped, basically.

46:52.885 --> 46:55.521
In all my years running a bar,

46:55.521 --> 46:57.590
now I'm getting treated
like a human trafficker.

47:01.727 --> 47:02.561
Sir.

47:03.863 --> 47:06.365
Nobody's going to eat you alive.

47:07.099 --> 47:08.501
You can wipe that look off your face.

47:10.870 --> 47:12.004
That handsome face.

47:12.671 --> 47:13.906
People might think...

47:14.573 --> 47:16.275
we've come to take your money.

47:19.778 --> 47:21.046
Will you all cut it out?

47:22.047 --> 47:24.817
If you're bored,
go somewhere else and get drunk.

47:25.217 --> 47:26.118
Why?

47:26.652 --> 47:27.987
Do you want me to introduce you
to a nice place?

47:33.592 --> 47:35.027
Sir, you're a funny guy.

47:52.545 --> 47:53.412
What,

47:54.280 --> 47:55.614
are you their fixer?

47:56.382 --> 47:57.716
And you're here to threaten me?

48:01.420 --> 48:02.488
Fine.

48:02.922 --> 48:04.890
I'm going to step into the kitchen now.

48:05.257 --> 48:06.592
I have to get ready for dinner service.

48:07.893 --> 48:09.728
But if I come back out here...

48:09.728 --> 48:11.330
and you're still pulling this crap,

48:13.899 --> 48:15.868
then I really won't be responsible
for what happens.

48:26.078 --> 48:27.880
That tiny little bastard.

48:27.880 --> 48:29.315
Take the guest out.

48:32.284 --> 48:34.286
You're making a mistake here.

48:35.020 --> 48:37.823
A guy who runs a bar
sure can't read the room.

48:38.924 --> 48:40.726
That little...

48:45.931 --> 48:47.099
Damn it.

48:58.844 --> 49:00.146
If you make one more sound,

49:00.146 --> 49:01.580
I'll snap this arm clean off.

49:03.048 --> 49:06.285
Why is it that you Korean bastards
never listen when someone's being nice?

49:08.921 --> 49:11.390
Do I have to tell you again
what it is I want to know?

49:11.824 --> 49:13.292
No, I'll talk.

49:13.292 --> 49:15.294
I'll tell you everything.

49:20.833 --> 49:22.067
Were you trying to look stylish?

49:22.401 --> 49:23.302
Yes.

49:24.670 --> 49:27.540
Koreans are weird.

49:28.107 --> 49:32.144
(Reflection)

49:38.517 --> 49:39.752
Eyes down.

49:40.119 --> 49:43.022
I'll crush everyone whose eyes are open.

49:47.126 --> 49:48.027
Where am I?

49:52.464 --> 49:54.166
You've been given a special job today.

49:54.600 --> 49:56.902
Teach this little punk a lesson.

49:57.436 --> 49:59.271
He drugged our decent people...

49:59.271 --> 50:00.840
and extorted money.

50:01.340 --> 50:03.642
The boss approved it,
so do whatever you want.

50:03.976 --> 50:05.344
Is he one of ours?

50:05.344 --> 50:06.245
No.

50:06.512 --> 50:07.713
He's a Korean gangster.

50:07.713 --> 50:09.281
Can I really do whatever I want?

50:09.682 --> 50:11.250
Do whatever you want. I'm leaving.

50:11.250 --> 50:12.151
No.

50:13.219 --> 50:14.320
Please don't go.

50:15.254 --> 50:16.622
Please spare me.

50:17.223 --> 50:19.391
Let go, you fat bastard.

50:24.129 --> 50:25.097
Sir.

50:28.300 --> 50:29.235
Sir.

50:30.336 --> 50:31.270
Pinky.

50:31.270 --> 50:32.338
This little punk...

50:32.771 --> 50:35.140
is the younger brother
of the site manager who picks on you.

50:40.079 --> 50:41.180
Sir.

50:41.180 --> 50:42.548
Sir!

50:51.023 --> 50:52.491
Well, look who it is.

50:53.792 --> 50:57.563
I'm going to squeeze
all that grease out of your gut today.

51:07.540 --> 51:09.208
What took you so long?

51:09.208 --> 51:10.776
I seriously thought I was going to die.

51:11.644 --> 51:13.412
I used every personal contact I had...

51:13.412 --> 51:14.847
and managed to track him down.

51:14.847 --> 51:16.882
These days, privacy laws are stricter,

51:16.882 --> 51:18.217
so if you get caught, you're finished.

51:19.084 --> 51:20.920
And because of this,

51:20.920 --> 51:23.022
I was not able to open the shop,
and normally, I'd bill that...

51:23.022 --> 51:25.624
You're sure it's Lee Jong Su, right?

51:25.624 --> 51:27.026
How many times do I have to tell you?

51:27.026 --> 51:28.594
I've been in this game for 30 years.

51:28.594 --> 51:29.461
Trust me.

51:29.862 --> 51:30.696
Right.

51:31.096 --> 51:32.965
Before I forget, take this first.

51:32.965 --> 51:34.466
I fixed it all, so it'll work fine now.

51:34.466 --> 51:36.068
Thank you.

51:37.770 --> 51:39.638
But is your real job
a repair shop owner...

51:39.638 --> 51:41.173
or a detective?

51:41.173 --> 51:44.009
Violent Crimes Unit One
at Dongdae Police Station.

51:44.009 --> 51:46.378
I'm the ace of the whole
major crimes squad.

51:46.745 --> 51:48.047
Then why...

51:49.248 --> 51:50.683
I did something and got fired.

51:51.984 --> 51:53.853
I didn't know that was that kind of money.

51:54.587 --> 51:56.322
After being unemployed
for about two years,

51:56.322 --> 51:57.756
my wife left with the kids,

51:58.290 --> 52:00.125
and she won't even give me a divorce.
It's driving me crazy.

52:02.094 --> 52:03.562
Did you get fired for taking bribes?

52:04.196 --> 52:06.298
Hey, what bribes?

52:06.699 --> 52:08.100
Don't go digging into the details.

52:12.872 --> 52:14.473
That's him.

52:18.410 --> 52:20.112
He's leaving now.

52:20.112 --> 52:21.514
You've seen this
in movies plenty of times, right?

52:21.514 --> 52:22.781
We're doing that now.

52:22.781 --> 52:23.616
Doing what?

52:23.616 --> 52:25.751
The good guys chasing the bad guy.

52:49.608 --> 52:51.677
But why is this car so slow?

52:52.144 --> 52:53.412
We're going to lose him.

52:53.412 --> 52:54.480
Lose him?

52:54.713 --> 52:56.715
With my driving,
this is already impressive.

52:58.484 --> 53:00.786
Lee Jong Su, that bastard.

53:01.787 --> 53:04.757
But what exactly is it
you need to find out from him?

53:05.157 --> 53:06.759
I want to do this job
knowing what's going on too.

53:08.194 --> 53:09.495
I can't tell you yet.

53:09.695 --> 53:10.830
You can't tell me?

53:10.830 --> 53:12.031
But you hired me for this case.

53:12.431 --> 53:14.166
You haven't forgotten who I am, have you?

53:14.633 --> 53:15.668
It's not that.

53:15.935 --> 53:17.436
I don't know yet either.

53:17.436 --> 53:18.504
What?

53:18.504 --> 53:20.072
You don't even know
why you're following him?

53:20.072 --> 53:22.174
I think Hee Su was being blackmailed.

53:22.975 --> 53:25.744
I asked what was going on,
but she wouldn't tell me.

53:25.978 --> 53:27.813
But Choi Hee Su is dead.

53:28.714 --> 53:31.650
Exactly, so we need to learn it
from the man who was threatening her.

53:31.650 --> 53:32.685
What are you talking about?

53:32.685 --> 53:34.587
You think that bastard
is just going to be easy?

53:35.120 --> 53:36.222
I don't have a choice.

53:36.689 --> 53:38.057
I have to find out, no matter what.

53:38.524 --> 53:39.859
With Choi Hee Su dead,

53:39.859 --> 53:41.060
what are you even going to do
once you know?

53:41.060 --> 53:42.795
The day Lee Jong Su came to the studio,

53:43.262 --> 53:44.697
both of them avoided me.

53:45.197 --> 53:46.098
Hey.

53:46.098 --> 53:48.467
Did I ever ask you for money like this?

53:48.467 --> 53:49.568
Who are you to give me money?

53:49.568 --> 53:50.636
Who do you think you are?

53:53.606 --> 53:54.440
Hey.

53:54.773 --> 53:56.108
- Who do you think you are to...
- No, Myo Jin, don't.

53:56.876 --> 53:59.044
Don't.

54:00.746 --> 54:02.548
- Hee Su.
- I'll contact you.

54:02.548 --> 54:04.316
I'll contact you. Just go.

54:10.456 --> 54:12.691
Choi Hee Su and Lee Jong Su? Why?

54:12.691 --> 54:14.660
He must know why that was.

54:15.494 --> 54:17.096
If both of them were avoiding me,

54:18.030 --> 54:19.665
then I must've been involved somehow.

54:19.665 --> 54:20.566
It better be true.

54:28.207 --> 54:29.041
I'm getting out.

54:51.297 --> 54:52.097
Did he go up?

54:54.400 --> 54:56.335
He stopped on the second floor.

54:56.602 --> 54:57.903
There's no time. Use the stairs.

55:05.077 --> 55:06.212
Hey, hide yourself over here.

55:06.612 --> 55:08.147
He can't see you right now.

55:09.248 --> 55:12.051
But what exactly are we going to do
after following him in here like this?

55:13.919 --> 55:15.754
He's heading inside
after finishing his conversation.

55:18.557 --> 55:20.526
He has his photo hanging at the entrance,

55:20.826 --> 55:21.861
so I guess he's the owner.

55:22.394 --> 55:23.262
What is that?

55:23.496 --> 55:24.530
A wine bar?

55:24.830 --> 55:26.131
Give me a break.

55:27.099 --> 55:28.067
But...

55:29.034 --> 55:30.669
where did that bastard
get that kind of money?

55:30.669 --> 55:32.705
What do we do now?

55:35.508 --> 55:36.475
Take this first.

55:37.143 --> 55:38.344
What's this?

55:38.777 --> 55:40.146
It's a cloning kit.

55:40.146 --> 55:41.580
Just plug in this cable,

55:41.580 --> 55:43.616
and the light comes on
and starts the copy.

55:43.883 --> 55:44.984
No matter how much data's on it,

55:44.984 --> 55:46.385
cloning a phone only takes about a minute.

55:47.453 --> 55:48.754
No.

55:48.754 --> 55:49.722
Was it two minutes?

55:49.722 --> 55:51.090
Anyway, simple, right?

55:51.090 --> 55:52.558
You want me to clone his phone?

55:52.992 --> 55:54.326
By myself?

55:54.860 --> 55:56.495
If you want to know about someone,

55:56.495 --> 55:58.297
you look at their phone.

55:58.297 --> 56:00.399
A person's whole life is in there.

56:00.399 --> 56:02.334
What if I get caught?

56:02.701 --> 56:03.802
I can't do something like this.

56:04.837 --> 56:05.704
Come on.

56:05.704 --> 56:07.339
So what, you're going
to walk up to him and say,

56:07.339 --> 56:10.009
"Hey, why were you threatening my friend?"

56:10.009 --> 56:12.244
And then he'll go,
"Well, here's the thing..."

56:12.244 --> 56:13.512
You think he'll answer like that?

56:13.512 --> 56:15.047
This is the only way...

56:15.047 --> 56:17.683
to find out what that bastard was up to.

56:20.085 --> 56:21.954
Then what am I supposed to do?

56:21.954 --> 56:24.356
First, figure out which room he's in.

56:24.356 --> 56:25.491
Come on, hurry.

56:25.491 --> 56:26.926
Go. Quick.

56:26.926 --> 56:27.726
But...

56:33.732 --> 56:34.733
Welcome.

56:36.769 --> 56:37.670
This way, please.

56:44.810 --> 56:46.912
Excuse me, where is the owner?

56:46.912 --> 56:48.681
He's in a consultation right now.

56:48.681 --> 56:49.849
Would you like me to let him know?

56:49.849 --> 56:52.384
No, it's okay. I can wait until he's done.

56:52.384 --> 56:54.253
Okay. Please call me when you've decided.

57:14.740 --> 57:16.742
You look even better
than the last time you came.

57:16.742 --> 57:17.476
Really?

57:17.476 --> 57:18.811
Then I guess the money was worth it.

57:20.579 --> 57:22.481
I look forward to your choice.

57:22.948 --> 57:24.416
Of course, I'll invest in it.

57:24.917 --> 57:26.986
Thanks to you again,

57:26.986 --> 57:29.054
I think everything
will go smoothly this time too.

57:32.892 --> 57:35.261
Hey! Who's the owner here?

57:35.461 --> 57:36.729
Get out here right now.

57:36.729 --> 57:38.264
Is it you?

57:38.264 --> 57:40.432
Excuse me, what seems to be the problem?

57:40.666 --> 57:41.634
I see.

57:42.201 --> 57:43.602
- So it's you.
- Goodness.

57:43.602 --> 57:45.371
You're the bastard...

57:45.371 --> 57:47.173
who talked my wife into divorcing me.

57:47.173 --> 57:48.641
What did you do to her...

57:48.641 --> 57:51.343
for her to slap divorce papers
down at the breakfast table?

57:51.343 --> 57:52.278
You bastard!

57:52.278 --> 57:53.379
Sir,

57:53.379 --> 57:55.614
you can't behave like this in here.

57:55.614 --> 57:57.283
Please calm down first,

57:57.283 --> 57:59.385
and let's go over there
and talk this through.

57:59.385 --> 58:00.352
Talk this through?

58:00.352 --> 58:01.353
Talk this through?

58:01.353 --> 58:03.189
Don't give me
that "talk this through" bullshit.

58:03.189 --> 58:05.324
And why am I your customer?

58:05.324 --> 58:06.458
I'm your customer's husband.

58:06.458 --> 58:08.527
The husband of the customer you seduced.

58:08.994 --> 58:09.962
Phone.

58:09.962 --> 58:11.263
What are you doing?

58:11.263 --> 58:12.531
You slept with my wife, didn't you?

58:12.531 --> 58:13.833
You thought I wouldn't know?

58:13.833 --> 58:15.201
Look at you. You can't even answer.

58:15.467 --> 58:16.936
You picked the wrong person, you bastard.

58:18.470 --> 58:19.772
How many times was it?

58:20.206 --> 58:22.208
How many times did you do it?

58:25.611 --> 58:26.479
Hey.

58:26.712 --> 58:29.315
My wife's eyes were so bloodshot
she went to the hospital,

58:29.315 --> 58:31.684
and they said she was addicted to wine,
you bastard!

58:31.684 --> 58:34.019
I'm saying, first let go of this,
and then we can talk.

58:34.453 --> 58:36.555
- What are you doing? Get him off me.
- Yes, sir.

58:36.555 --> 58:37.857
Don't do this.

58:37.857 --> 58:38.891
You ruined me,

58:38.891 --> 58:40.726
took my wife and my money,

58:40.726 --> 58:41.894
and you think you'll get away with it?

58:41.894 --> 58:43.162
You really messed
with the wrong guy, you bastard.

58:43.162 --> 58:44.396
What are you even saying?

58:44.930 --> 58:46.332
Hey, let go of this.

58:46.332 --> 58:48.701
I'm going to throw all of you in prison.

58:48.701 --> 58:49.502
Let go.

58:50.035 --> 58:51.003
Come on.

58:51.003 --> 58:52.938
(Downloading 31 percent)

58:55.341 --> 58:56.275
What do I do?

58:57.009 --> 58:58.744
My luck is terrible today.

58:58.744 --> 59:00.980
Of all days,
some complete psycho has to show up.

59:00.980 --> 59:02.414
(Downloading 46 percent)

59:02.414 --> 59:04.216
Get over here!
Where are you running off to?

59:04.216 --> 59:06.752
Hey, you!
You slept with my wife, didn't you?

59:06.752 --> 59:08.053
You thought I wouldn't know?

59:08.053 --> 59:09.321
Look at you. You can't even answer.

59:10.189 --> 59:11.090
Come on.

59:12.691 --> 59:14.426
How many times?

59:14.426 --> 59:15.194
How many times did you do it?

59:15.194 --> 59:16.662
So you really did sleep with her?

59:16.662 --> 59:17.630
Hey.

59:19.265 --> 59:20.299
You little...

59:20.299 --> 59:21.200
Let go!

59:22.768 --> 59:23.836
(Uploading 82 percent)

59:27.706 --> 59:28.507
(Uploading 96 percent)

59:31.977 --> 59:32.945
Who are you?

59:33.712 --> 59:34.513
What?

59:36.282 --> 59:37.550
Well...

59:40.452 --> 59:42.388
How reckless of you to come here.

59:42.855 --> 59:44.023
Let go of this.

59:44.023 --> 59:45.758
Just let go.

59:45.758 --> 59:47.560
I'm a cop.

59:47.827 --> 59:50.062
Boss, this person's a cop.

59:51.363 --> 59:52.598
- What?
- You're all dead today.

59:52.598 --> 59:53.833
You assaulted a police officer.

59:53.833 --> 59:54.834
You little...

59:54.834 --> 59:55.968
What? Let go of that.

01:00:00.072 --> 01:00:00.873
Sir.

01:00:08.247 --> 01:00:09.315
Sir.

01:00:09.315 --> 01:00:10.249
Are you okay?

01:00:12.218 --> 01:00:13.819
Wang Gi Cheol, that bastard.

01:00:14.186 --> 01:00:15.554
We can't let him get away now.

01:00:16.388 --> 01:00:17.690
Okay.

01:00:20.292 --> 01:00:21.093
Damn it.

01:00:25.598 --> 01:00:26.732
Mr. Lee Jong Su.

01:00:36.575 --> 01:00:37.476
Hey.

01:00:37.476 --> 01:00:38.644
Just a second.

01:00:45.618 --> 01:00:46.452
Damn it.

01:00:52.291 --> 01:00:53.225
Damn it!

01:00:53.492 --> 01:00:54.860
I have something to ask you.

01:00:55.561 --> 01:00:56.795
It'll just take a second.

01:01:15.181 --> 01:01:16.015
Excuse me.

01:01:18.384 --> 01:01:19.351
You vicious bitch.

01:01:21.487 --> 01:01:22.488
Wasn't it enough...

01:01:23.389 --> 01:01:24.623
that two people died?

01:01:26.892 --> 01:01:28.127
You could've stopped there...

01:01:29.161 --> 01:01:30.196
with your revenge.

01:02:11.136 --> 01:02:15.207
(REVERSE)

01:02:15.407 --> 01:02:16.575
Check what messages they exchanged,

01:02:16.575 --> 01:02:18.043
and the answer will be clear.

01:02:18.043 --> 01:02:20.012
You killed my mom and dad?

01:02:20.012 --> 01:02:22.848
I didn't think she'd find out this fast.

01:02:22.848 --> 01:02:24.850
Then what am I supposed to do?

01:02:25.284 --> 01:02:26.418
Stop her.

01:02:26.418 --> 01:02:28.621
You handled the Jebudo Island
villa explosion case, didn't you?

01:02:28.621 --> 01:02:30.789
It was all complete bullshit.

01:02:30.789 --> 01:02:32.158
You don't need to be curious.

01:02:32.158 --> 01:02:34.059
If you know, it puts us both in danger.

01:02:34.059 --> 01:02:35.227
Thanks to that, it all clicked.

01:02:35.227 --> 01:02:38.063
I now know what was happening
without me knowing.

01:02:39.064 --> 01:02:40.900
There's someone else besides us...

01:02:40.900 --> 01:02:42.234
who's after Ham Myo Jin?

01:02:43.422 --> 01:02:45.422
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
